sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant D as Directory Service
    participant K as Kafka/Event Bus
    participant C as EmployeeLifecycleConsumer
    participant P as ProvisioningApplicationService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant E as Email Service
    participant A as Audit Platform

    D->>K: employee.reactivated
    K->>C: deliver event
    C->>P: synchronizeEmployeeStatus(event)
    P->>DB: BEGIN
    P->>DB: lock user by employeeRef
    P->>DB: revoke old pending invitations
    P->>DB: invalidate/reset credential according to product policy
    P->>DB: User -> INVITED; securityVersion++
    P->>P: create new invitation token/hash
    P->>DB: insert Invitation(PENDING)
    P->>DB: COMMIT
    P->>E: send new invitation
    P->>A: employee.reactivated + invitation.created
    C-->>K: ACK

    Note over P,DB: This diagram applies the PRD default assumption: reactivation requires a new invitation and does not silently revive old credentials.
